    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1895-03-13T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1895-03-13T00:00:00-05:00" n="111" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d111">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Uhl</persName> to Baron
                                    <persName type="to">Fava</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1895-03-13">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13,
                                1895</hi>.</date>
                    </dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 8.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">My Dear Baron</hi>: Your note of to-day’s date
                            relating to the press reports of the killing of four Italian laborers at
                            Walsenburg, Colo., has been received.</p>
                <p>I have telegraphed the governor of Colorado for information on the
                            subject, and upon receipt of a reply from him will promptly advise
                            you.</p>
                <p>Very truly, yours,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Edwin F. Uhl</hi>,<lb/>
                        <hi rend="italic">Acting Secretary.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
